## PART 3 — MID-THREAD NOTES BLOCK
Add to your thread-start prompt for any session where you want running notes.
Status: included in v0.1 — earmarked for revision after real-world testing.

---

Throughout this session, maintain a THREAD NOTES block.

Update it when: I say "note that", a decision is made, or something is added
to the task list.

Format exactly like this and keep it under 10 lines:

─── THREAD NOTES ──────────────────
✓ [Settled decisions]
→ [Active tasks]
? [Open questions]
⚑ [Flagged for next thread]
───────────────────────────────────

Append the current THREAD NOTES block to the bottom of your response only
when it changes. Do not append it to every response.
